13std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module> parse_bitcode_file(llvm::StringRef buf, llvm::LLVMContext *context, const char *id) {
14
15 llvm::MemoryBufferRef bitcode_buffer = llvm::MemoryBufferRef(buf, id);
16
17 auto ret_val = llvm::expectedToErrorOr(
18 llvm::parseBitcodeFile(bitcode_buffer, *context));
19 if (!ret_val) {
20 internal_error << "Could not parse built-in bitcode file " << id
21 << " llvm error is " << ret_val.getError() << "\n";
22 }
23
24 std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module> result(std::move(*ret_val));
25 result->setModuleIdentifier(id);
26
27 return result;
28}
29
30#define DECLARE_INITMOD(mod) \
31 extern "C" unsigned char halide_internal_initmod_##mod[]; \
32 extern "C" int halide_internal_initmod_##mod##_length; \
33 std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module> get_initmod_##mod(llvm::LLVMContext *context) { \
34 llvm::StringRef sb = llvm::StringRef((const char *)halide_internal_initmod_##mod, \
35 halide_internal_initmod_##mod##_length); \
36 return parse_bitcode_file(sb, context, #mod); \
37 }
38
39#define DECLARE_NO_INITMOD(mod) \
40 std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module> get_initmod_##mod(llvm::LLVMContext *, bool = false, bool = false) { \
41 user_error << "Halide was compiled without support for this target\n"; \
42 return std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module>(); \
43 } \
44 std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module> get_initmod_##mod##_ll(llvm::LLVMContext *) { \
45 user_error << "Halide was compiled without support for this target\n"; \
46 return std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module>(); \
47 }
48
49#define DECLARE_CPP_INITMOD_LOOKUP(mod) \
50 std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module> get_initmod_##mod(llvm::LLVMContext *context, bool bits_64, bool debug) { \
51 if (bits_64) { \
52 if (debug) { \
53 return get_initmod_##mod##_64_debug(context); \
54 } else { \
55 return get_initmod_##mod##_64(context); \
56 } \
57 } else { \
58 if (debug) { \
59 return get_initmod_##mod##_32_debug(context); \
60 } else { \
61 return get_initmod_##mod##_32(context); \
62 } \
63 } \
64 }

66#define DECLARE_CPP_INITMOD(mod) \
67 DECLARE_INITMOD(mod##_32_debug) \
68 DECLARE_INITMOD(mod##_64_debug) \
69 DECLARE_INITMOD(mod##_32) \
70 DECLARE_INITMOD(mod##_64) \
71 DECLARE_CPP_INITMOD_LOOKUP(mod)
72
73#define DECLARE_LL_INITMOD(mod) \
74 DECLARE_INITMOD(mod##_ll)

288llvm::DataLayout get_data_layout_for_target(Target target) {
289 if (target.arch == Target::X86) {
290 if (target.bits == 32) {
291 if (target.os == Target::OSX) {
292 return llvm::DataLayout("e-m:o-p:32:32-p270:32:32-p271:32:32-p272:64:64-f64:32:64-f80:128-n8:16:32-S128");
293 } else if (target.os == Target::IOS) {
294 return llvm::DataLayout("e-m:o-p:32:32-p270:32:32-p271:32:32-p272:64:64-f64:32:64-f80:128-n8:16:32-S128");
295 } else if (target.os == Target::Windows && !target.has_feature(Target::JIT)) {
296 return llvm::DataLayout("e-m:x-p:32:32-p270:32:32-p271:32:32-p272:64:64-i64:64-f80:32-n8:16:32-a:0:32-S32");
297 } else if (target.os == Target::Windows) {
298 return llvm::DataLayout("e-m:e-p:32:32-p270:32:32-p271:32:32-p272:64:64-i64:64-f80:32-n8:16:32-a:0:32-S32");
299 } else {
300 // Linux/Android
301 return llvm::DataLayout("e-m:e-p:32:32-p270:32:32-p271:32:32-p272:64:64-f64:32:64-f80:32-n8:16:32-S128");
302 }
303 } else { // 64-bit
304 if (target.os == Target::OSX) {
305 return llvm::DataLayout("e-m:o-p270:32:32-p271:32:32-p272:64:64-i64:64-f80:128-n8:16:32:64-S128");
306 } else if (target.os == Target::IOS) {
307 return llvm::DataLayout("e-m:o-p270:32:32-p271:32:32-p272:64:64-i64:64-f80:128-n8:16:32:64-S128");
308 } else if (target.os == Target::Windows && !target.has_feature(Target::JIT)) {
309 return llvm::DataLayout("e-m:w-p270:32:32-p271:32:32-p272:64:64-i64:64-f80:128-n8:16:32:64-S128");
310 } else if (target.os == Target::Windows) {
311 return llvm::DataLayout("e-m:e-p270:32:32-p271:32:32-p272:64:64-i64:64-f80:128-n8:16:32:64-S128");
312 } else {
313 return llvm::DataLayout("e-m:e-p270:32:32-p271:32:32-p272:64:64-i64:64-f80:128-n8:16:32:64-S128");
314 }
315 }
316 } else if (target.arch == Target::ARM) {
317 if (target.bits == 32) {
318 if (target.os == Target::IOS) {
319 return llvm::DataLayout("e-m:o-p:32:32-Fi8-f64:32:64-v64:32:64-v128:32:128-a:0:32-n32-S32");
320 } else {
321 return llvm::DataLayout("e-m:e-p:32:32-Fi8-i64:64-v128:64:128-a:0:32-n32-S64");
322 }
323 } else { // 64-bit
324 if (target.os == Target::IOS) {
325 return llvm::DataLayout("e-m:o-i64:64-i128:128-n32:64-S128");
326 } else if (target.os == Target::OSX) {
327 return llvm::DataLayout("e-m:o-i64:64-i128:128-n32:64-S128");
328 } else if (target.os == Target::Windows) {
329 return llvm::DataLayout("e-m:w-p:64:64-i32:32-i64:64-i128:128-n32:64-S128");
330 } else {
331 return llvm::DataLayout("e-m:e-i8:8:32-i16:16:32-i64:64-i128:128-n32:64-S128");
332 }
333 }
334 } else if (target.arch == Target::MIPS) {
335 if (target.bits == 32) {
336 return llvm::DataLayout("e-m:m-p:32:32-i8:8:32-i16:16:32-i64:64-n32-S64");
337 } else {
338 return llvm::DataLayout("e-m:m-i8:8:32-i16:16:32-i64:64-n32:64-S128");
339 }
340 } else if (target.arch == Target::POWERPC) {
341 if (target.bits == 32) {
342 return llvm::DataLayout("e-m:e-i32:32-n32");
343 } else {
344 return llvm::DataLayout("e-m:e-i64:64-n32:64");
345 }
346 } else if (target.arch == Target::Hexagon) {
347 return llvm::DataLayout(
348 "e-m:e-p:32:32:32-a:0-n16:32-i64:64:64-i32:32:32-i16:16:16-i1:8:8"
349 "-f32:32:32-f64:64:64-v32:32:32-v64:64:64-v512:512:512-v1024:1024:1024-v2048:2048:2048");
350 } else if (target.arch == Target::WebAssembly) {
351 if (target.bits == 32) {
352 return llvm::DataLayout("e-m:e-p:32:32-i64:64-n32:64-S128");
353 } else {
354 return llvm::DataLayout("e-m:e-p:64:64-i64:64-n32:64-S128");
355 }
356 } else if (target.arch == Target::RISCV) {
357 // TODO: Valdidate this data layout is correct for RISCV. Assumption is it is like MIPS.
358 if (target.bits == 32) {
359 return llvm::DataLayout("e-m:e-p:32:32-i64:64-n32-S128");
360 } else {
361 return llvm::DataLayout("e-m:e-p:64:64-i64:64-i128:128-n64-S128");
362 }
363 } else {
364 internal_error << "Bad target arch: " << target.arch << "\n";
365 return llvm::DataLayout("unreachable");
366 }
367}

373llvm::Triple get_triple_for_target(const Target &target) {
374 llvm::Triple triple;
375
376 if (target.arch == Target::X86) {
377 if (target.bits == 32) {
378 triple.setArch(llvm::Triple::x86);
379 } else {
380 user_assert(target.bits == 64) << "Target must be 32- or 64-bit.\n";
381 triple.setArch(llvm::Triple::x86_64);
382 }
383
384 if (target.os == Target::Linux) {
385 triple.setOS(llvm::Triple::Linux);
386 triple.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::GNU);
387 } else if (target.os == Target::OSX) {
388 triple.setVendor(llvm::Triple::Apple);
389 triple.setOS(llvm::Triple::MacOSX);
390 } else if (target.os == Target::Windows) {
391 triple.setVendor(llvm::Triple::PC);
392 triple.setOS(llvm::Triple::Win32);
393 triple.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::MSVC);
394 if (target.has_feature(Target::JIT)) {
395 // Use ELF for jitting
396 triple.setObjectFormat(llvm::Triple::ELF);
397 }
398 } else if (target.os == Target::Android) {
399 triple.setOS(llvm::Triple::Linux);
400 triple.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::Android);
401 } else if (target.os == Target::IOS) {
402 // X86 on iOS for the simulator
403 triple.setVendor(llvm::Triple::Apple);
404 triple.setOS(llvm::Triple::IOS);
405 } else if (target.os == Target::Fuchsia) {
406 triple.setOS(llvm::Triple::Fuchsia);
407 }
408 } else if (target.arch == Target::ARM) {
409 if (target.bits == 32) {
410 if (target.has_feature(Target::ARMv7s)) {
411 triple.setArchName("armv7s");
412 } else {
413 triple.setArch(llvm::Triple::arm);
414 }
415 } else {
416 user_assert(target.bits == 64) << "Target bits must be 32 or 64\n";
417#ifdef WITH_AARCH64
418 triple.setArch(llvm::Triple::aarch64);
419#else
420 user_error << "AArch64 llvm target not enabled in this build of Halide\n";
421#endif
422 }
423
424 if (target.os == Target::Android) {
425 triple.setOS(llvm::Triple::Linux);
426 triple.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::EABI);
427 } else if (target.os == Target::IOS) {
428 triple.setOS(llvm::Triple::IOS);
429 triple.setVendor(llvm::Triple::Apple);
430 } else if (target.os == Target::Linux) {
431 triple.setOS(llvm::Triple::Linux);
432 triple.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::GNUEABIHF);
433 } else if (target.os == Target::Windows) {
434 user_assert(target.bits == 64) << "Windows ARM targets must be 64-bit.\n";
435 triple.setVendor(llvm::Triple::PC);
436 triple.setOS(llvm::Triple::Win32);
437 triple.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::MSVC);
438 if (target.has_feature(Target::JIT)) {
439 // TODO(shoaibkamil): figure out a way to test this.
440 // Currently blocked by https://github.com/halide/Halide/issues/5040
441 user_error << "No JIT support for this OS/CPU combination yet.\n";
442 }
443 } else if (target.os == Target::Fuchsia) {
444 triple.setOS(llvm::Triple::Fuchsia);
445 } else if (target.os == Target::OSX) {
446 triple.setVendor(llvm::Triple::Apple);
447 triple.setOS(llvm::Triple::MacOSX);
448 triple.setArchName("arm64");
449 } else if (target.os == Target::NoOS) {
450 // For bare-metal environments
451
452 } else {
453 user_error << "No arm support for this OS\n";
454 }
455 } else if (target.arch == Target::MIPS) {
456 // Currently MIPS support is only little-endian.
457 if (target.bits == 32) {
458 triple.setArch(llvm::Triple::mipsel);
459 } else {
460 user_assert(target.bits == 64) << "Target must be 32- or 64-bit.\n";
461 triple.setArch(llvm::Triple::mips64el);
462 }
463
464 if (target.os == Target::Android) {
465 triple.setOS(llvm::Triple::Linux);
466 triple.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::Android);
467 } else {
468 user_error << "No mips support for this OS\n";
469 }
470 } else if (target.arch == Target::POWERPC) {
471#ifdef WITH_POWERPC
472 // Only ppc*-unknown-linux-gnu are supported for the time being.
473 user_assert(target.os == Target::Linux) << "PowerPC target is Linux-only.\n";
474 triple.setVendor(llvm::Triple::UnknownVendor);
475 triple.setOS(llvm::Triple::Linux);
476 triple.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::GNU);
477 if (target.bits == 32) {
478 triple.setArch(llvm::Triple::ppc);
479 } else {
480 // Currently POWERPC64 support is only little-endian.
481 user_assert(target.bits == 64) << "Target must be 32- or 64-bit.\n";
482 triple.setArch(llvm::Triple::ppc64le);
483 }
484#else
485 user_error << "PowerPC llvm target not enabled in this build of Halide\n";
486#endif
487 } else if (target.arch == Target::Hexagon) {
488 triple.setVendor(llvm::Triple::UnknownVendor);
489 triple.setArch(llvm::Triple::hexagon);
490 triple.setObjectFormat(llvm::Triple::ELF);
491 } else if (target.arch == Target::WebAssembly) {
492 triple.setVendor(llvm::Triple::UnknownVendor);
493 if (target.bits == 32) {
494 triple.setArch(llvm::Triple::wasm32);
495 } else {
496 triple.setArch(llvm::Triple::wasm64);
497 }
498 triple.setObjectFormat(llvm::Triple::Wasm);
499 } else if (target.arch == Target::RISCV) {
500 if (target.bits == 32) {
501 triple.setArch(llvm::Triple::riscv32);
502 } else {
503 user_assert(target.bits == 64) << "Target must be 32- or 64-bit.\n";
504 triple.setArch(llvm::Triple::riscv64);
505 }
506
507 if (target.os == Target::Linux) {
508 triple.setOS(llvm::Triple::Linux);
509 // TODO: Check what options there are here.
510 triple.setEnvironment(llvm::Triple::GNUEABIHF);
511 } else if (target.os == Target::NoOS) {
512 // for baremetal environment
513 } else {
514 user_error << "No RISCV support for this OS\n";
515 }
516 } else {
517 internal_error << "Bad target arch: " << target.arch << "\n";
518 }
519
520 return triple;
521}

527void convert_weak_to_linkonce(llvm::GlobalValue &gv) {
528 llvm::GlobalValue::LinkageTypes linkage = gv.getLinkage();
529 if (linkage == llvm::GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage) {
530 gv.setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceAnyLinkage);
531 } else if (linkage == llvm::GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage) {
532 gv.setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage);
533 } else if (linkage == llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalWeakLinkage) {
534 gv.setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage);
535 }
536}
537
538// Link all modules together and with the result in modules[0], all
539// other input modules are destroyed. Sets the datalayout and target
540// triple appropriately for the target.
541void link_modules(std::vector<std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module>> &modules, Target t,
542 bool allow_stripping_all_weak_functions = false) {
543 llvm::DataLayout data_layout = get_data_layout_for_target(t);
544 llvm::Triple triple = Internal::get_triple_for_target(t);
545
546 // Set the layout and triple on the modules before linking, so
547 // llvm doesn't complain while combining them.
548 for (size_t i = 0; i < modules.size(); i++) {
549 if (t.os == Target::Windows &&
550 !Internal::starts_with(modules[i]->getName().str(), "windows_")) {
551 // When compiling for windows, all wchars are
552 // 16-bit. Generic modules may have it set to 32-bit. Drop
553 // any module flags on the generic modules and use the
554 // more correct ones on the windows-specific modules to
555 // avoid a conflict. This is safe as long as the generic
556 // modules never actually use a wchar.
557 if (auto *module_flags = modules[i]->getModuleFlagsMetadata()) {
558 modules[i]->eraseNamedMetadata(module_flags);
559 }
560 }
561 modules[i]->setDataLayout(data_layout);
562 modules[i]->setTargetTriple(triple.str());
563 }
564
565 // Link them all together
566 for (size_t i = 1; i < modules.size(); i++) {
567 bool failed = llvm::Linker::linkModules(*modules[0],
568 std::move(modules[i]));
569 if (failed) {
570 internal_error << "Failure linking initial modules\n";
571 }
572 }
573
574 // Now re-mark most weak symbols as linkonce. They are only weak to
575 // prevent llvm from stripping them during initial module
576 // assembly. This means they can be stripped later.
577
578 // The symbols that we might want to call as a user even if not
579 // used in the Halide-generated code must remain weak. This is
580 // handled automatically by assuming any symbol starting with
581 // "halide_" that is weak will be retained. There are a few
582 // symbols for which this convention is not followed and these are
583 // in this set.
584 const std::set<string> retain = {"__stack_chk_guard",
585 "__stack_chk_fail"};
586
587 // COMDAT is not supported in MachO object files, hence it does
588 // not work on Mac OS or iOS. These sometimes show up in the
589 // runtime since we compile for an abstract target that is based
590 // on ELF. This code removes all Comdat items and leaves the
591 // symbols they were attached to as regular definitions, which
592 // only works if there is a single instance, which is generally
593 // the case for the runtime. Presumably if this isn't true,
594 // linking the module will fail.
595 //
596 // Comdats are left in for other platforms as they are required
597 // for certain things on Windows and they are useful in general in
598 // ELF based formats.
599 if (t.os == Target::IOS || t.os == Target::OSX) {
600 for (auto &global_obj : modules[0]->global_objects()) {
601 global_obj.setComdat(nullptr);
602 }
603 modules[0]->getComdatSymbolTable().clear();
604 }
605
606 // Enumerate the global variables.
607 for (auto &gv : modules[0]->globals()) {
608 // No variables are part of the public interface (even the ones labelled halide_)
609 convert_weak_to_linkonce(gv);
610 }
611
612 // Enumerate the functions.
613 for (auto &f : *modules[0]) {
614 const std::string f_name = Internal::get_llvm_function_name(f);
615
616 bool is_halide_extern_c_sym = Internal::starts_with(f_name, "halide_");
617 internal_assert(!is_halide_extern_c_sym || f.isWeakForLinker() || f.isDeclaration())
618 << " for function " << f_name << "\n";
619
620 // We never want *any* Function marked as external-weak here;
621 // convert all of those to plain external.
622 if (f.getLinkage() == llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalWeakLinkage) {
623 f.setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage);
624 } else {
625 const bool can_strip = !is_halide_extern_c_sym && retain.count(f_name) == 0;
626 if (can_strip || allow_stripping_all_weak_functions) {
627 convert_weak_to_linkonce(f);
628 }
629 }
630
631 // Windows requires every symbol that's going to get merged
632 // has a comdat that specifies how. The linkage type alone
633 // isn't enough.
634 if (t.os == Target::Windows && f.isWeakForLinker()) {
635 llvm::Comdat *comdat = modules[0]->getOrInsertComdat(f_name);
636 comdat->setSelectionKind(llvm::Comdat::Any);
637 f.setComdat(comdat);
638 }
639 }
640
641 // Now remove the force-usage global that prevented clang from
642 // dropping functions from the initial module.
643 llvm::GlobalValue *llvm_used = modules[0]->getNamedGlobal("llvm.used");
644 if (llvm_used) {
645 llvm_used->eraseFromParent();
646 }
647
648 llvm::GlobalValue *llvm_compiler_used =
649 modules[0]->getNamedGlobal("llvm.compiler.used");
650 if (llvm_compiler_used) {
651 llvm_compiler_used->eraseFromParent();
652 }
653
654 // Also drop the dummy runtime api usage. We only needed it so
655 // that the declarations are retained in the module during the
656 // linking procedure above.
657 llvm::GlobalValue *runtime_api =
658 modules[0]->getNamedGlobal("halide_runtime_api_functions");
659 if (runtime_api) {
660 runtime_api->eraseFromParent();
661 }
662}
663
664} // namespace
665
666namespace Internal {
667
668/** When JIT-compiling on 32-bit windows, we need to rewrite calls
669 * to name-mangled win32 api calls to non-name-mangled versions.
670 */
671void undo_win32_name_mangling(llvm::Module *m) {
672 llvm::IRBuilder<> builder(m->getContext());
673 // For every function prototype...
674 for (llvm::Module::iterator iter = m->begin(); iter != m->end(); ++iter) {
675 llvm::Function &f = *iter;
676 string n = get_llvm_function_name(f);
677 // if it's a __stdcall call that starts with \01_, then we're making a win32 api call
678 if (f.getCallingConv() == llvm::CallingConv::X86_StdCall &&
679 f.empty() &&
680 n.size() > 2 && n[0] == 1 && n[1] == '_') {
681
682 // Unmangle the name.
683 string unmangled_name = n.substr(2);
684 size_t at = unmangled_name.rfind('@');
685 unmangled_name = unmangled_name.substr(0, at);
686
687 // Extern declare the unmangled version.
688 llvm::Function *unmangled = llvm::Function::Create(f.getFunctionType(), f.getLinkage(), unmangled_name, m);
689 unmangled->setCallingConv(f.getCallingConv());
690
691 // Add a body to the mangled version that calls the unmangled version.
692 llvm::BasicBlock *block = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(m->getContext(), "entry", &f);
693 builder.SetInsertPoint(block);
694
695 vector<llvm::Value *> args;
696 for (auto &arg : f.args()) {
697 args.push_back(&arg);
698 }
699
700 llvm::CallInst *c = builder.CreateCall(unmangled, args);
701 c->setCallingConv(f.getCallingConv());
702
703 if (f.getReturnType()->isVoidTy()) {
704 builder.CreateRetVoid();
705 } else {
706 builder.CreateRet(c);
707 }
708 }
709 }
710}
711
712void add_underscore_to_posix_call(llvm::CallInst *call, llvm::Function *fn, llvm::Module *m) {
713 string new_name = "_" + fn->getName().str();
714 llvm::Function *alt = m->getFunction(new_name);
715 if (!alt) {
716 alt = llvm::Function::Create(fn->getFunctionType(),
717 llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage,
718 new_name, m);
719 }
720 internal_assert(alt->getName() == new_name);
721 call->setCalledFunction(alt);
722}
723
724/** Windows uses _close, _open, _write, etc instead of the posix
725 * names. Defining stubs that redirect causes mis-compilations inside
726 * of mcjit, so we just rewrite uses of these functions to include an
727 * underscore. */
728void add_underscores_to_posix_calls_on_windows(llvm::Module *m) {
729 string posix_fns[] = {"vsnprintf", "open", "close", "write", "fileno"};
730
731 string *posix_fns_begin = posix_fns;
732 string *posix_fns_end = posix_fns + sizeof(posix_fns) / sizeof(posix_fns[0]);
733
734 for (auto &fn : *m) {
735 for (auto &basic_block : fn) {
736 for (auto &instruction : basic_block) {
737 if (llvm::CallInst *call = llvm::dyn_cast<llvm::CallInst>(&instruction)) {
738 if (llvm::Function *called_fn = call->getCalledFunction()) {
739 if (std::find(posix_fns_begin, posix_fns_end, called_fn->getName()) != posix_fns_end) {
740 add_underscore_to_posix_call(call, called_fn, m);
741 }
742 }
743 }
744 }
745 }
746 }
747}
748
749std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module> link_with_wasm_jit_runtime(llvm::LLVMContext *c, const Target &t,
750 std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module> extra_module) {
751 bool bits_64 = (t.bits == 64);
752 bool debug = t.has_feature(Target::Debug);
753
754 // We only need to include things that must be linked in as callable entrypoints;
755 // things that are 'alwaysinline' can be included here but are unnecessary.
756 vector<std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module>> modules;
757 modules.push_back(std::move(extra_module));
758 modules.push_back(get_initmod_fake_thread_pool(c, bits_64, debug));
759 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_allocator(c, bits_64, debug));
760 modules.push_back(get_initmod_halide_buffer_t(c, bits_64, debug));
761 modules.push_back(get_initmod_destructors(c, bits_64, debug));
762 // These two aren't necessary, since they are 100% alwaysinline
763 // modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_math_ll(c));
764 // modules.push_back(get_initmod_wasm_math_ll(c));
765 modules.push_back(get_initmod_tracing(c, bits_64, debug));
766 modules.push_back(get_initmod_cache(c, bits_64, debug));
767 modules.push_back(get_initmod_to_string(c, bits_64, debug));
768 modules.push_back(get_initmod_alignment_32(c, bits_64, debug));
769 modules.push_back(get_initmod_device_interface(c, bits_64, debug));
770 modules.push_back(get_initmod_metadata(c, bits_64, debug));
771 modules.push_back(get_initmod_float16_t(c, bits_64, debug));
772 modules.push_back(get_initmod_errors(c, bits_64, debug));
773 modules.push_back(get_initmod_msan_stubs(c, bits_64, debug));
774
775 // We don't want anything marked as weak for the wasm-jit runtime,
776 // so convert all of them to linkonce
777 constexpr bool allow_stripping_all_weak_functions = true;
778 link_modules(modules, t, allow_stripping_all_weak_functions);
779
780 return std::move(modules[0]);
781}

783/** Create an llvm module containing the support code for a given target. */
784std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module> get_initial_module_for_target(Target t, llvm::LLVMContext *c, bool for_shared_jit_runtime, bool just_gpu) {
785 enum InitialModuleType {
786 ModuleAOT,
787 ModuleAOTNoRuntime,
788 ModuleJITShared,
789 ModuleJITInlined,
790 ModuleGPU
791 } module_type;
792
793 if (t.has_feature(Target::JIT)) {
794 if (just_gpu) {
795 module_type = ModuleGPU;
796 } else if (for_shared_jit_runtime) {
797 module_type = ModuleJITShared;
798 } else {
799 module_type = ModuleJITInlined;
800 }
801 } else if (t.has_feature(Target::NoRuntime)) {
802 module_type = ModuleAOTNoRuntime;
803 } else {
804 module_type = ModuleAOT;
805 }
806
807 // Halide::Internal::debug(0) << "Getting initial module type " << (int)module_type << "\n";
808
809 internal_assert(t.bits == 32 || t.bits == 64)
810 << "Bad target: " << t.to_string();
811 bool bits_64 = (t.bits == 64);
812 bool debug = t.has_feature(Target::Debug);
813 bool tsan = t.has_feature(Target::TSAN);
814
815 vector<std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module>> modules;
816
817 if (module_type != ModuleGPU) {
818 if (module_type != ModuleJITInlined && module_type != ModuleAOTNoRuntime) {
819 // OS-dependent modules
820 if (t.os == Target::Linux) {
821 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_allocator(c, bits_64, debug));
822 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_error_handler(c, bits_64, debug));
823 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_print(c, bits_64, debug));
824 if (t.arch == Target::X86) {
825 modules.push_back(get_initmod_linux_clock(c, bits_64, debug));
826 } else {
827 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_clock(c, bits_64, debug));
828 }
829 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_io(c, bits_64, debug));
830 modules.push_back(get_initmod_linux_host_cpu_count(c, bits_64, debug));
831 modules.push_back(get_initmod_linux_yield(c, bits_64, debug));
832 if (tsan) {
833 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_threads_tsan(c, bits_64, debug));
834 } else {
835 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_threads(c, bits_64, debug));
836 }
837 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_get_symbol(c, bits_64, debug));
838 } else if (t.os == Target::WebAssemblyRuntime) {
839 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_allocator(c, bits_64, debug));
840 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_error_handler(c, bits_64, debug));
841 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_print(c, bits_64, debug));
842 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_clock(c, bits_64, debug));
843 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_io(c, bits_64, debug));
844 modules.push_back(get_initmod_linux_host_cpu_count(c, bits_64, debug));
845 modules.push_back(get_initmod_linux_yield(c, bits_64, debug));
846 if (t.has_feature(Target::WasmThreads)) {
847 // Assume that the wasm libc will be providing pthreads
848 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_threads(c, bits_64, debug));
849 } else {
850 modules.push_back(get_initmod_fake_thread_pool(c, bits_64, debug));
851 }
852 modules.push_back(get_initmod_fake_get_symbol(c, bits_64, debug));
853 } else if (t.os == Target::OSX) {
854 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_allocator(c, bits_64, debug));
855 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_error_handler(c, bits_64, debug));
856 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_print(c, bits_64, debug));
857 modules.push_back(get_initmod_osx_clock(c, bits_64, debug));
858 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_io(c, bits_64, debug));
859 modules.push_back(get_initmod_osx_host_cpu_count(c, bits_64, debug));
860 modules.push_back(get_initmod_osx_yield(c, bits_64, debug));
861 if (tsan) {
862 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_threads_tsan(c, bits_64, debug));
863 } else {
864 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_threads(c, bits_64, debug));
865 }
866 modules.push_back(get_initmod_osx_get_symbol(c, bits_64, debug));
867 modules.push_back(get_initmod_osx_host_cpu_count(c, bits_64, debug));
868 } else if (t.os == Target::Android) {
869 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_allocator(c, bits_64, debug));
870 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_error_handler(c, bits_64, debug));
871 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_print(c, bits_64, debug));
872 if (t.arch == Target::ARM) {
873 modules.push_back(get_initmod_android_clock(c, bits_64, debug));
874 } else {
875 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_clock(c, bits_64, debug));
876 }
877 modules.push_back(get_initmod_android_io(c, bits_64, debug));
878 modules.push_back(get_initmod_android_host_cpu_count(c, bits_64, debug));
879 modules.push_back(get_initmod_linux_yield(c, bits_64, debug)); // TODO: verify
880 if (tsan) {
881 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_threads_tsan(c, bits_64, debug));
882 } else {
883 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_threads(c, bits_64, debug));
884 }
885 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_get_symbol(c, bits_64, debug));
886 } else if (t.os == Target::Windows) {
887 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_allocator(c, bits_64, debug));
888 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_error_handler(c, bits_64, debug));
889 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_print(c, bits_64, debug));
890 modules.push_back(get_initmod_windows_clock(c, bits_64, debug));
891 modules.push_back(get_initmod_windows_io(c, bits_64, debug));
892 modules.push_back(get_initmod_windows_yield(c, bits_64, debug));
893 if (tsan) {
894 modules.push_back(get_initmod_windows_threads_tsan(c, bits_64, debug));
895 } else {
896 modules.push_back(get_initmod_windows_threads(c, bits_64, debug));
897 }
898 modules.push_back(get_initmod_windows_get_symbol(c, bits_64, debug));
899 } else if (t.os == Target::IOS) {
900 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_allocator(c, bits_64, debug));
901 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_error_handler(c, bits_64, debug));
902 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_print(c, bits_64, debug));
903 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_clock(c, bits_64, debug));
904 modules.push_back(get_initmod_ios_io(c, bits_64, debug));
905 modules.push_back(get_initmod_osx_host_cpu_count(c, bits_64, debug));
906 modules.push_back(get_initmod_osx_yield(c, bits_64, debug));
907 if (tsan) {
908 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_threads_tsan(c, bits_64, debug));
909 } else {
910 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_threads(c, bits_64, debug));
911 }
912 } else if (t.os == Target::QuRT) {
913 modules.push_back(get_initmod_qurt_allocator(c, bits_64, debug));
914 modules.push_back(get_initmod_qurt_yield(c, bits_64, debug));
915 if (tsan) {
916 modules.push_back(get_initmod_qurt_threads_tsan(c, bits_64, debug));
917 } else {
918 modules.push_back(get_initmod_qurt_threads(c, bits_64, debug));
919 }
920 modules.push_back(get_initmod_qurt_init_fini(c, bits_64, debug));
921 } else if (t.os == Target::NoOS) {
922 // The OS-specific symbols provided by the modules
923 // above are expected to be provided by the containing
924 // process instead at link time. Less aggressive than
925 // NoRuntime, as OS-agnostic modules like tracing are
926 // still included below.
927 if (t.arch == Target::Hexagon) {
928 modules.push_back(get_initmod_qurt_allocator(c, bits_64, debug));
929 }
930 modules.push_back(get_initmod_fake_thread_pool(c, bits_64, debug));
931 } else if (t.os == Target::Fuchsia) {
932 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_allocator(c, bits_64, debug));
933 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_error_handler(c, bits_64, debug));
934 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_print(c, bits_64, debug));
935 modules.push_back(get_initmod_fuchsia_clock(c, bits_64, debug));
936 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_io(c, bits_64, debug));
937 modules.push_back(get_initmod_fuchsia_host_cpu_count(c, bits_64, debug));
938 modules.push_back(get_initmod_fuchsia_yield(c, bits_64, debug));
939 if (tsan) {
940 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_threads_tsan(c, bits_64, debug));
941 } else {
942 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_threads(c, bits_64, debug));
943 }
944 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_get_symbol(c, bits_64, debug));
945 }
946 }
947
948 if (module_type != ModuleJITShared) {
949 // The first module for inline only case has to be C/C++ compiled otherwise the
950 // datalayout is not properly setup.
951 modules.push_back(get_initmod_halide_buffer_t(c, bits_64, debug));
952 modules.push_back(get_initmod_destructors(c, bits_64, debug));
953 modules.push_back(get_initmod_pseudostack(c, bits_64, debug));
954 // Math intrinsics vary slightly across platforms
955 if (t.os == Target::Windows) {
956 if (t.bits == 32) {
957 modules.push_back(get_initmod_win32_math_ll(c));
958 } else {
959 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_math_ll(c));
960 }
961 } else {
962 modules.push_back(get_initmod_posix_math_ll(c));
963 }
964 }
965
966 if (module_type != ModuleJITInlined && module_type != ModuleAOTNoRuntime) {
967 // These modules are always used and shared
968 modules.push_back(get_initmod_gpu_device_selection(c, bits_64, debug));
969 if (t.arch != Target::Hexagon) {
970 // These modules don't behave correctly on a real
971 // Hexagon device (they do work in the simulator
972 // though...).
973 modules.push_back(get_initmod_tracing(c, bits_64, debug));
974 modules.push_back(get_initmod_trace_helper(c, bits_64, debug));
975 modules.push_back(get_initmod_write_debug_image(c, bits_64, debug));
976
977 // TODO: Support this module in the Hexagon backend,
978 // currently generates assert at src/HexagonOffload.cpp:279
979 modules.push_back(get_initmod_cache(c, bits_64, debug));
980 }
981 modules.push_back(get_initmod_to_string(c, bits_64, debug));
982
983 if (t.arch == Target::Hexagon ||
984 t.has_feature(Target::HVX)) {
985 modules.push_back(get_initmod_alignment_128(c, bits_64, debug));
986 } else if (t.arch == Target::X86) {
987 // AVX-512 requires 64-byte alignment. Could only increase alignment
988 // if AVX-512 is in the target, but that falls afoul of linking
989 // multiple versions of a filter for different levels of x86 -- weak
990 // linking will pick one of the alignment modules unpredictably.
991 // Another way to go is to query the CPU features and align by
992 // 64 oonly if the procesor has AVX-512.
993 // The choice to go 64 all the time is for simplicity and on the idea
994 // that it won't be a noticeable cost in the majority of x86 usage.
995 modules.push_back(get_initmod_alignment_64(c, bits_64, debug));
996 } else {
997 modules.push_back(get_initmod_alignment_32(c, bits_64, debug));
998 }
999
1000 modules.push_back(get_initmod_allocation_cache(c, bits_64, debug));
1001 modules.push_back(get_initmod_device_interface(c, bits_64, debug));
1002 modules.push_back(get_initmod_metadata(c, bits_64, debug));
1003 modules.push_back(get_initmod_float16_t(c, bits_64, debug));
1004 modules.push_back(get_initmod_errors(c, bits_64, debug));
1005
1006 // Some environments don't support the atomics the profiler requires.
1007 if (t.arch != Target::MIPS && t.os != Target::NoOS && t.os != Target::QuRT) {
1008 if (t.os == Target::Windows) {
1009 modules.push_back(get_initmod_windows_profiler(c, bits_64, debug));
1010 } else {
1011 modules.push_back(get_initmod_profiler(c, bits_64, debug));
1012 }
1013 }
1014
1015 if (t.has_feature(Target::MSAN)) {
1016 modules.push_back(get_initmod_msan(c, bits_64, debug));
1017 } else {
1018 modules.push_back(get_initmod_msan_stubs(c, bits_64, debug));
1019 }
1020 }
1021
1022 if (module_type != ModuleJITShared) {
1023 // These modules are optional
1024 if (t.arch == Target::X86) {
1025 modules.push_back(get_initmod_x86_ll(c));
1026 }
1027 if (t.arch == Target::ARM) {
1028 if (t.bits == 64) {
1029 modules.push_back(get_initmod_aarch64_ll(c));
1030 } else if (t.has_feature(Target::ARMv7s)) {
1031 modules.push_back(get_initmod_arm_ll(c));
1032 } else if (!t.has_feature(Target::NoNEON)) {
1033 modules.push_back(get_initmod_arm_ll(c));
1034 } else {
1035 modules.push_back(get_initmod_arm_no_neon_ll(c));
1036 }
1037 }
1038 if (t.arch == Target::MIPS) {
1039 modules.push_back(get_initmod_mips_ll(c));
1040 }
1041 if (t.arch == Target::POWERPC) {
1042 modules.push_back(get_initmod_powerpc_ll(c));
1043 }
1044 if (t.arch == Target::Hexagon) {
1045 modules.push_back(get_initmod_qurt_hvx(c, bits_64, debug));
1046 modules.push_back(get_initmod_hvx_128_ll(c));
1047 if (t.features_any_of({Target::HVX_v65, Target::HVX_v66})) {
1048 modules.push_back(get_initmod_qurt_hvx_vtcm(c, bits_64,
1049 debug));
1050 }
1051
1052 } else {
1053 modules.push_back(get_initmod_prefetch(c, bits_64, debug));
1054 }
1055 if (t.has_feature(Target::SSE41)) {
1056 modules.push_back(get_initmod_x86_sse41_ll(c));
1057 }
1058 if (t.has_feature(Target::AVX)) {
1059 modules.push_back(get_initmod_x86_avx_ll(c));
1060 }
1061 if (t.has_feature(Target::AVX2)) {
1062 modules.push_back(get_initmod_x86_avx2_ll(c));
1063 }
1064 if (t.has_feature(Target::AVX512)) {
1065 modules.push_back(get_initmod_x86_avx512_ll(c));
1066 }
1067 if (t.has_feature(Target::Profile)) {
1068 user_assert(t.os != Target::WebAssemblyRuntime) << "The profiler cannot be used in a threadless environment.";
1069 modules.push_back(get_initmod_profiler_inlined(c, bits_64, debug));
1070 }
1071 if (t.arch == Target::WebAssembly) {
1072 modules.push_back(get_initmod_wasm_math_ll(c));
1073 }
1074 }
1075
1076 if (module_type == ModuleAOT) {
1077 // These modules are only used for AOT compilation
1078 modules.push_back(get_initmod_can_use_target(c, bits_64, debug));
1079 if (t.arch == Target::X86) {
1080 modules.push_back(get_initmod_x86_cpu_features(c, bits_64, debug));
1081 }
1082 if (t.arch == Target::ARM) {
1083 if (t.bits == 64) {
1084 modules.push_back(get_initmod_aarch64_cpu_features(c, bits_64, debug));
1085 } else {
1086 modules.push_back(get_initmod_arm_cpu_features(c, bits_64, debug));
1087 }
1088 }
1089 if (t.arch == Target::MIPS) {
1090 modules.push_back(get_initmod_mips_cpu_features(c, bits_64, debug));
1091 }
1092 if (t.arch == Target::POWERPC) {
1093 modules.push_back(get_initmod_powerpc_cpu_features(c, bits_64, debug));
1094 }
1095 if (t.arch == Target::Hexagon) {
1096 modules.push_back(get_initmod_hexagon_cpu_features(c, bits_64, debug));
1097 }
1098 if (t.arch == Target::RISCV) {
1099 modules.push_back(get_initmod_riscv_cpu_features(c, bits_64, debug));
1100 }
1101 if (t.arch == Target::WebAssembly) {
1102 modules.push_back(get_initmod_wasm_cpu_features(c, bits_64, debug));
1103 }
1104 }
1105 }
1106
1107 if (module_type == ModuleJITShared || module_type == ModuleGPU) {
1108 modules.push_back(get_initmod_module_jit_ref_count(c, bits_64, debug));
1109 } else if (module_type == ModuleAOT) {
1110 modules.push_back(get_initmod_module_aot_ref_count(c, bits_64, debug));
1111 }
1112
1113 if (module_type == ModuleAOT || module_type == ModuleGPU) {
1114 if (t.has_feature(Target::CUDA)) {
1115 if (t.os == Target::Windows) {
1116 modules.push_back(get_initmod_windows_cuda(c, bits_64, debug));
1117 } else {
1118 modules.push_back(get_initmod_cuda(c, bits_64, debug));
1119 }
1120 }
1121 if (t.has_feature(Target::OpenCL)) {
1122 if (t.os == Target::Windows) {
1123 modules.push_back(get_initmod_windows_opencl(c, bits_64, debug));
1124 } else {
1125 modules.push_back(get_initmod_opencl(c, bits_64, debug));
1126 }
1127 }
1128 if (t.has_feature(Target::OpenGLCompute)) {
1129 modules.push_back(get_initmod_openglcompute(c, bits_64, debug));
1130 if (t.os == Target::Android) {
1131 // Only platform that supports OpenGL Compute for now.
1132 modules.push_back(get_initmod_opengl_egl_context(c, bits_64, debug));
1133 } else if (t.os == Target::Linux) {
1134 if (t.has_feature(Target::EGL)) {
1135 modules.push_back(get_initmod_opengl_egl_context(c, bits_64, debug));
1136 } else {
1137 modules.push_back(get_initmod_opengl_glx_context(c, bits_64, debug));
1138 }
1139 } else if (t.os == Target::OSX) {
1140 modules.push_back(get_initmod_osx_opengl_context(c, bits_64, debug));
1141 } else {
1142 // You're on your own to provide definitions of halide_opengl_get_proc_address and halide_opengl_create_context
1143 }
1144 }
1145 if (t.has_feature(Target::Metal)) {
1146 modules.push_back(get_initmod_metal(c, bits_64, debug));
1147 if (t.arch == Target::ARM) {
1148 modules.push_back(get_initmod_metal_objc_arm(c, bits_64, debug));
1149 } else if (t.arch == Target::X86) {
1150 modules.push_back(get_initmod_metal_objc_x86(c, bits_64, debug));
1151 } else {
1152 user_error << "Metal can only be used on ARM or X86 architectures.\n";
1153 }
1154 }
1155 if (t.has_feature(Target::D3D12Compute)) {
1156 user_assert(bits_64) << "D3D12Compute target only available on 64-bit targets for now.\n";
1157 user_assert(t.os == Target::Windows) << "D3D12Compute target only available on Windows targets.\n";
1158 if (t.arch == Target::X86) {
1159 modules.push_back(get_initmod_windows_d3d12compute_x86(c, bits_64, debug));
1160 } else if (t.arch == Target::ARM) {
1161 modules.push_back(get_initmod_windows_d3d12compute_arm(c, bits_64, debug));
1162 } else {
1163 user_error << "Direct3D 12 can only be used on ARM or X86 architectures.\n";
1164 }
1165 }
1166 if (t.arch != Target::Hexagon && t.has_feature(Target::HVX)) {
1167 modules.push_back(get_initmod_module_jit_ref_count(c, bits_64, debug));
1168 modules.push_back(get_initmod_hexagon_host(c, bits_64, debug));
1169 }
1170 if (t.has_feature(Target::HexagonDma)) {
1171 modules.push_back(get_initmod_hexagon_cache_allocator(c, bits_64, debug));
1172 modules.push_back(get_initmod_hexagon_dma(c, bits_64, debug));
1173 modules.push_back(get_initmod_hexagon_dma_pool(c, bits_64, debug));
1174 }
1175 }
1176
1177 if (module_type == ModuleAOT && t.has_feature(Target::Matlab)) {
1178 modules.push_back(get_initmod_matlab(c, bits_64, debug));
1179 }
1180
1181 if (module_type == ModuleAOTNoRuntime ||
1182 module_type == ModuleJITInlined ||
1183 t.os == Target::NoOS) {
1184 modules.push_back(get_initmod_runtime_api(c, bits_64, debug));
1185 }
1186
1187 link_modules(modules, t);
1188
1189 if (t.os == Target::Windows &&
1190 t.bits == 32 &&
1191 (t.has_feature(Target::JIT))) {
1192 undo_win32_name_mangling(modules[0].get());
1193 }
1194
1195 if (t.os == Target::Windows) {
1196 add_underscores_to_posix_calls_on_windows(modules[0].get());
1197 }
1198
1199 return std::move(modules[0]);
1200}
1201
1202#ifdef WITH_NVPTX
1203std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module> get_initial_module_for_ptx_device(Target target, llvm::LLVMContext *c) {
1204 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module>> modules;
1205 modules.push_back(get_initmod_ptx_dev_ll(c));
1206
1207 std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module> module;
1208
1209 // This table is based on the guidance at:
1210 // http://docs.nvidia.com/cuda/libdevice-users-guide/basic-usage.html#linking-with-libdevice
1211 if (target.has_feature(Target::CUDACapability35)) {
1212 module = get_initmod_ptx_compute_35_ll(c);
1213 } else if (target.features_any_of({Target::CUDACapability32,
1214 Target::CUDACapability50})) {
1215 // For some reason sm_32 and sm_50 use libdevice 20
1216 module = get_initmod_ptx_compute_20_ll(c);
1217 } else if (target.has_feature(Target::CUDACapability30)) {
1218 module = get_initmod_ptx_compute_30_ll(c);
1219 } else {
1220 module = get_initmod_ptx_compute_20_ll(c);
1221 }
1222 modules.push_back(std::move(module));
1223
1224 link_modules(modules, target);
1225
1226 // For now, the PTX backend does not handle calling functions. So mark all functions
1227 // AvailableExternally to ensure they are inlined or deleted.
1228 for (llvm::Module::iterator iter = modules[0]->begin(); iter != modules[0]->end(); iter++) {
1229 llvm::Function &f = *iter;
1230
1231 // This is intended to set all definitions (not extern declarations)
1232 // to "available externally" which should guarantee they do not exist
1233 // after the resulting module is finalized to code. That is they must
1234 // be inlined to be used.
1235 //
1236 // However libdevice has a few routines that are marked
1237 // "noinline" which must either be changed to alow inlining or
1238 // preserved in generated code. This preserves the intent of
1239 // keeping these routines out-of-line and hence called by
1240 // not marking them AvailableExternally.
1241
1242 if (!f.isDeclaration() && !f.hasFnAttribute(llvm::Attribute::NoInline)) {
1243 f.setLinkage(llvm::GlobalValue::AvailableExternallyLinkage);
1244 }
1245 }
1246
1247 llvm::Triple triple("nvptx64--");
1248 modules[0]->setTargetTriple(triple.str());
1249
1250 llvm::DataLayout dl("e-i64:64-v16:16-v32:32-n16:32:64");
1251 modules[0]->setDataLayout(dl);
1252
1253 return std::move(modules[0]);
1254}
1255#endif
1256
1257void add_bitcode_to_module(llvm::LLVMContext *context, llvm::Module &module,
1258 const std::vector<uint8_t> &bitcode, const std::string &name) {
1259 llvm::StringRef sb = llvm::StringRef((const char *)&bitcode[0], bitcode.size());
1260 std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module> add_in = parse_bitcode_file(sb, context, name.c_str());
1261
1262 bool failed = llvm::Linker::linkModules(module, std::move(add_in));
1263 if (failed) {
1264 internal_error << "Failure linking in additional module: " << name << "\n";
1265 }
1266}
